The paper discusses the formal specification and verification of separation kernels, which are fundamental software for safety and security-critical systems. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the correctness of the kernel, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses formal methods for verification, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO).
